        <span class="bf-rule"></span>
        <span class="bf-label">Below the Fold &middot; The Five Articles</span>
        <span class="bf-rule"></span>
      </section>

      <article class="banner banner-paper" aria-label="The Paper">
        <header class="banner-head">
          <span class="banner-num">I.</span>
          <p class="banner-eyebrow">The Paper &middot; Article &sect; I</p>
        </header>
        <div class="banner-body">
          <div class="banner-text">
            <h3 class="banner-headline">Five Results. Three Theorems. One Replacement.</h3>
            <p class="banner-deck"><em>Entropy Replacement and Complexity-Sensitive Complementarity in Non-Isometric Holographic Codes.</em></p>
            <p class="banner-lede">The featured paper, Paper III. Two observers disagree; the hard quantum disagreement reduces, provably, to a classical one; the random case is now unconditional; the integer gap stands.</p>
            <div class="banner-cta">
              <a class="btn-primary" href="/paper">Read the Paper</a>
              <a class="btn-secondary" href="/paper/paper3.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener">PDF</a>
            </div>
          </div>
          <aside class="banner-side">
            <ul class="banner-stats">
              <li><span class="stat-n">5</span> <span class="stat-l">Results</span></li>
              <li><span class="stat-n">3</span> <span class="stat-l">Theorems</span></li>
              <li><span class="stat-n">1</span> <span class="stat-l">Replacement</span></li>
              <li><span class="stat-n">1</span> <span class="stat-l">Integer Gap</span></li>
            </ul>
            <p class="banner-caption">
              <span class="banner-caption-eyebrow">Submitted</span>
              May MMXXVI, headed for arXiv.<br />Reviewed by Scholar (ChatGPT).
            </p>
          </aside>
        </div>
      </article>

      <!-- ━━ II. THE EVOLUTION (banner) ━━ -->
      <article class="banner banner-paper" aria-label="The Evolution">
        <header class="banner-head">
          <span class="banner-num">II.</span>
          <p class="banner-eyebrow">The Evolution &middot; Article &sect; II</p>
        </header>
        <div class="banner-body">
          <div class="banner-text">
            <h3 class="banner-headline">One Paper Became Three. Watch It Walk Upright.</h3>
            <p class="banner-deck"><em>Pl. I &middot; The Ascent of the Donkey, in Five Figures.</em></p>
            <p class="banner-lede">The five-figure ascent from beast to gentleman. Paper I as it first stood, Paper II as it was sharpened, Paper III as it now stands &mdash; what each got, what each was missing, and the reviewer who drove the last advance.</p>
            <div class="banner-cta">
              <a class="btn-primary" href="/evolution">Walk the Evolution</a>
            </div>
          </div>
          <aside class="banner-side">
            <figure class="plate" style="max-width:320px;margin:0 auto;">
              <div class="plate-inner">
                <img src="/images/evolution.png" alt="Five stages from beast to gentleman: a donkey at the cliff's edge, rising by degrees, until it walks upright in a frock coat and bowler." />
              </div>
            </figure>
          </aside>
        </div>
      </article>

      <!-- ━━ III. THE CURRICULUM + IV. FIELD NOTES (two-up) ━━ -->
      <section class="duo" aria-label="Curriculum and Field Notes">

        <article class="duo-card duo-curriculum">
          <header class="duo-head">
            <span class="duo-num">III.</span>
            <p class="duo-eyebrow">The Curriculum &middot; Article &sect; III</p>
          </header>
          <h3 class="duo-headline">Physics 101 to Quantum Gravity, Mapped.</h3>
          <p class="duo-deck">The full path of study, drawn as a Victorian railway chart. Thirty-eight stations on six lines, from Newtonian mechanics to the speculative frontier. All routes terminate at the papers.</p>
          <figure class="duo-map">
            <div class="duo-map-frame" aria-hidden="true">
              <svg viewBox="0 0 360 200" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" role="img" aria-label="Decorative chart of curriculum lines">
                <path d="M 24 100 L 320 100" stroke="#211810" stroke-width="6" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round"/>
                <path d="M 24 100 L 24 48 L 200 48" stroke="#8A1818" stroke-width="3" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
                <path d="M 80 100 L 80 158 L 250 158" stroke="#8A1818" stroke-width="2.5" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
                <path d="M 200 100 L 200 70 L 280 70 L 280 100" stroke="#211810" stroke-width="2" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-dasharray="6,4"/>
                <path d="M 100 100 L 100 178 L 260 178 L 320 100" stroke="#211810" stroke-width="2.5" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
                <g fill="#211810">
                  <circle cx="24"  cy="100" r="5"/>
                  <circle cx="80"  cy="100" r="4"/>
                  <circle cx="140" cy="100" r="4"/>
                  <circle cx="200" cy="100" r="5"/>
                  <circle cx="260" cy="100" r="4"/>
                </g>
                <g fill="#8A1818">
                  <circle cx="24"  cy="48" r="4"/>
                  <circle cx="100" cy="48" r="4"/>
                  <circle cx="200" cy="48" r="4"/>
                  <circle cx="80"  cy="158" r="4"/>
                  <circle cx="170" cy="158" r="4"/>
                  <circle cx="250" cy="158" r="4"/>
                </g>
                <circle cx="320" cy="100" r="14" fill="none" stroke="#5C0E0E" stroke-width="2"/>
                <circle cx="320" cy="100" r="9"  fill="none" stroke="#5C0E0E" stroke-width="1.2"/>
                <circle cx="320" cy="100" r="5"  fill="#5C0E0E"/>
                <text x="320" y="36" text-anchor="middle" font-family="'IM Fell DW Pica SC', serif" font-size="11" letter-spacing="1.2" fill="#5C0E0E">PAPERS</text>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <figcaption>Pl. II &middot; A Chart of the Curriculum &middot; Six lines, thirty-eight stations</figcaption>
          </figure>
          <a class="duo-cta" href="/curriculum">Study the Map &rsaquo;</a>
        </article>

        <article class="duo-card duo-field-notes">
          <header class="duo-head">
            <span class="duo-num">IV.</span>
            <p class="duo-eyebrow">Field Notes &middot; Article &sect; IV</p>
          </header>
          <h3 class="duo-headline">The Notebook, Open. The Wrong Turns, Kept.</h3>
          <p class="duo-deck">Phase memos, work posts, and essays &mdash; now including twelve new entries on the road from Paper II to Paper III: the corrected foundation, the covariance that lied, the constant we refused to leave to the machine, and a new plain-English companion, <em>Alice and Bob</em>.</p>
          <blockquote class="duo-quote">
            <p>&ldquo;It is not that the universe has one answer for how much two observers can disagree. It has a <em>hierarchy</em> of answers, indexed by how structured the thing they are looking at is. And we can actually compute the hierarchy.&rdquo;</p>
            <cite>From <a href="/field-notes/a-little-help-for-my-friends">A Little Help for My Friends</a></cite>
          </blockquote>
          <a class="duo-cta" href="/field-notes">Open the Notebook &rsaquo;</a>
        </article>

      </section>

      <!-- ━━ FROM THE WIRE ━━ -->
      <aside class="dispatches" aria-labelledby="dispatches-head">
        <div class="dispatches-frame">
          <span class="dispatches-corner dispatches-corner-left">
            <span class="dispatches-corner-text">Latest</span>
          </span>
          <span class="dispatches-corner dispatches-corner-right">
            <span class="dispatches-corner-text">Dispatches</span>
          </span>
          <h3 class="dispatches-head" id="dispatches-head">From the Wire</h3>
          <div class="dispatches-rule" aria-hidden="true">
            <span class="dispatches-rule-line"></span>
            <span class="dispatches-rule-mark">&#10086;</span>
            <span class="dispatches-rule-line"></span>
          </div>
          <div class="dispatches-grid">
            <div class="dispatch-item">
              <p class="dispatch-date">MMXXVI &middot; V &middot; XXX</p>
              <p class="dispatch-body"><strong>Paper&nbsp;III complete.</strong> The entropy-replacement theorem closes the gap; the Haar law is now unconditional; Appendix C.6 closed with no numerical constant. Reviewed by Scholar across six rounds. Headed for arXiv.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="dispatch-item">
              <p class="dispatch-date">MMXXVI &middot; V &middot; XVIII</p>
              <p class="dispatch-body"><strong>Paper&nbsp;II.</strong> The structural identity is corrected &mdash; the averaged observer state is the <em>diagonal</em> of the bulk marginal. The foundation is sound; the central assumption remains.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="dispatch-item">
              <p class="dispatch-date">MMXXVI &middot; V &middot; XI</p>
              <p class="dispatch-body"><strong>Paper&nbsp;I complete.</strong> Five results, three theorems, headed for arXiv pending number assignment.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="dispatch-item">
              <p class="dispatch-date">MMXXVI &middot; IV &middot; XXIII</p>
              <p class="dispatch-body"><strong>Investigation begins.</strong> A man in Bend, Oregon asks Claude where to start with quantum mechanics. The walk to the frontier opens.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="dispatches-foot">
            <span class="pulse" aria-hidden="true"></span>
            <span>The research continues. Updated as it happens.</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <!-- ━━ V. THE METHOD (compact secondary, full-width) ━━ -->
      <section class="secondaries" aria-label="Method">
        <a href="/method" class="secondary">
          <div class="secondary-num">V.</div>
          <div class="secondary-body">
            <p class="secondary-eyebrow">The Method</p>
            <h3 class="secondary-headline">On the Doing of This Sort of Work.</h3>
            <p class="secondary-deck">The thesis, the protocol, the calibration log &mdash; now with a method section for each paper, and the methodological advance of Paper III: an external adversarial reviewer.</p>
          </div>
          <span class="secondary-arrow">&rsaquo;</span>
        </a>
      </section>

    </main>
